headline: Donald Trump’s Executive Order Maintains the Pain on UnitedHealth Stock (UNH)
summary: UnitedHealth (UNH) has experienced significant volatility, with its stock down approximately 55% from its 52-week high. Once viewed as a stable blue-chip stalwart, the company trades more like a distressed asset amid a series of negative developments. Rising medical costs, an unexpected CEO departure, and heightened regulatory uncertainty stemming from former President Trump’s recent executive order on drug pricing have all contributed to investor unease. headline: CI Q1 Earnings Call: Cigna Delivers Revenue Beat and Focuses on Healthcare Innovation
summary: Health insurance company Cigna (NYSE:CI) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 14.4% year on year to $65.5 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $6.74 per share was 6.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
